						<summary>

						

						<p>On a pillar set up in front of the Doḍḍa Mallēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1224, Śubhakṛit, Vaiśākha śu. [3], Monday = 1302 A.D., April 2.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records that Paiṁḍi Māṟṟeḍḍi, son of Bīra Muttiraḍḍi of Chintapalli set up an image of Muktīśvara in the temple of Doḍḍa Mallināthadēva and planted a <hi rend="italic">kalaśa</hi> in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
